-- Sen Dodd says may end TARP early to pay for reform
-- 
-- Tue Jun 29, 2010 2:45pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2010/06/29/us-financnial-regulation-dodd-idUSTRE65S5BZ20100629

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Senate Banking Committee Chairman Christopher Dodd said on Tuesday that lawmakers were considering ending the $700 billion bank bailout program early to pay for a financial regulatory overhaul. 

 "The plan it so reconvene the conference later this afternoon, the idea being the elimination of TARP ... except for the existing obligations," he told reporters. (Reporting by  Susan Cornwell )